io.spine.query

Class CustomColumn<S,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.query.CustomColumn<S,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - the type of objects serving as a source for the column values
    V - the type of column values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Column<S,V>

    @SPI
 @Immutable
public abstract class CustomColumn<S,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Column<S,V>
    A column storing the data which is not directly declared as a field in the Message of an EntityState or a plain record.

    End-users may choose to store some arbitrary or computed on-the-fly data along with the record. E.g. the time of entity creation or the role of the user created the record etc. That is, something which isn't included into the definition of the Message type of the record.

    The framework users would need to provide their own CustomColumn implementation. When storing objects with custom columns, the values are fetched according to the valueIn(S) implementation. In it, the S value represents an arbitrary object serving as a source for the value.

    See Also:
    CustomSubjectParameter, QueryPredicate.customParameters()
